<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - HEATER
        CORE - BLEND-AIR SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601402" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HEATER CORE - BLEND-AIR SYSTEM</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain engine cooling system.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cover from passenger side of instrument panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cover from Blend-Air unit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen hose clamps at heater core.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open Blend-Air door.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove heater core mounting screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601413">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601413" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601413" filename="../figg16/G1601413.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="392px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13. Air Conditioning Models, Heater Core Removal - Note Mounting Screws (3)
                    </caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect hoses from the heater core and pull the core outward (toward the rear of the
                    vehicle) to remove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove gaskets from ends of the heater core.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect hose and gaskets and if damaged or deteriorated, replace.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the gaskets on the ends of the heater core.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open the Blend-Air door.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the heater core. Align the slot tab on the lower inner corner of the heater core
                    with the button head rivet on the lower inner frame of the housing and push the heater core into
                    position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the heater core mounting screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect hoses to the heater core and tighten hose clamps.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refill engine cooling system.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set temperature control knob to HOT. Operate engine and check for coolant leaks and
                    coolant flow through the heater core.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
